org.bonitasoft.engine.bpm.process

Interface DesignProcessDefinition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseElement, BonitaObject, NamedElement, ProcessDefinition, Serializable

    public interface DesignProcessDefinition
extends ProcessDefinition
    Represents the Design Definition of a process. It gives access to process attributes.
    • display name
    • description
    • parameters
    • actors
    • search indexes
    Since:
    6.0.0
    Version:
    6.3.5
    Author:
    Matthieu Chaffotte, Celine Souchet, Laurent Leseigneur

      • getStringIndexLabel

        String getStringIndexLabel(int index)
        Retrieves the label for the ProcessDefinition given search index.

        You can define up to five search indexes for a process. See more at Define a search index Bonitasoft documentation page

        Parameters:
        index - The position of search index to retrieve. Valid values are between 1 and 5 (inclusive)
        Returns:
        The label the Expression of the search index
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if index is invalid
